<h4>Writing a basic ruleset</h4>

<h5>Selectors</h5>
<p>A css ruleset starts with a <em>selector</em> that defines which html elements the styles will be applied to. In this example the <code>p</code> (paragraph) element is the selector. The styles we add inside the <code>{}</code> brackets will apply to all <code>p</code> tags on the page.
<div class='dark'>


